@page
@model FiyiStackWeb.Areas.FiyiStack.Pages.LearnMoreModel
@{
    Layout = "_Layout";
}
<div class="container">
    <div class="row mt-5">
        <!-- Title -->
        <div class="col-lg-8 mx-auto text-center my-5">
            <h3 class="display-4">Learn more</h3>
            <h5>About FiyiStack and RAD tools</h5>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="container">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col">
            <div class="card bg-secondary">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title">Table of contents</h5>
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-8">
                            <ol>
                                <li class="mt-2"><a href="#1">What is FiyiStack?</a></li>
                                <li class="mt-2"><a href="#2">What is a RAD tool?</a></li>
                                <li class="mt-2"><a href="#3">What generates FiyiStack?</a></li>
                                <li class="mt-2"><a href="#4">The languages that FiyiStack works with</a></li>
                            </ol>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-4 d-none d-lg-inline d-xl-inline">
                            <img src="/img/FiyiStack/FiyiStackImageTransparent.png" width="130" alt="Logo" />
                        </div>
                    </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="card bg-secondary" id="1">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title">1. What is FiyiStack?</h5>
                    <p>
                        FiyiStack is a <span class="badge badge-success">low-code generator</span> that allows you to 
                        create a table, belonging to a database, and convert it into code to be manipulated by a web application. 
                        If you enter 10 columns of a table, FiyiStack 
                        <span class="badge badge-success">converts them to ~5,000 lines of code</span>. 
                        Thanks to this, <span class="badge badge-success">you can write code faster and more securely</span>. 
                        But this is not new, FiyiStack belongs to the range of programming tools as are the RAD tools. 
                        But, what is a RAD tool?
                    </p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="card bg-secondary" id="2">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title">2. What is a RAD tool?</h5>
                    <p>A RAD tool is a programming tool capable of <span class="badge badge-success">speeding up software development</span>. It's basic qualities are:</p> 
                    <ul>
                        <li class="mt-2">Rapid development and delivery with 
                            <span class="badge badge-success">high quality</span> for a low
                            investment cost system.</li>
                        <li class="mt-2">Reduce the risks of mistyping by developers, breaking the code into small fragments
                            to <span class="badge badge-success">provide easier change</span> during the development process.</li>
                        <li class="mt-2">Iteration and reuse of prototypes and templates.</li>
                        <li class="mt-2">Promotes the co-participation of clients with the development team.</li>
                        <li class="mt-2">It includes GUI builders, database builders, fourth generation languages,
                            and object-oriented techniques.</li>
                        <li class="mt-2">It emphasizes the <span class="badge badge-success">fulfillment of the requirements</span>
                            by the users.
                        </li>
                        <li class="mt-2">Development of priorities and definitions of delivery deadlines.</li>
                        <li class="mt-2">Produces the necessary documentation to facilitate future
                            development and maintenance.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <div class="alert alert-success alert-dismissible fade show" role="alert">
                        <span class="alert-inner--icon"><i class="ni ni-like-2"></i></span>
                        <span class="alert-inner--text">FiyiStack meets these qualities</span>
                    </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="card bg-secondary" id="3">
                <img class="card-img-top" src="/img/FiyiStack/Stack.png" alt="Stack">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title">3. What generates FiyiStack?</h5>
                    <p> 
                        A web application is composed of <span class="badge badge-success">3 main layers</span>. Front-end, back-end and
                        database. FiyiStack generates the 3 layers:
                    </p>
                    <p><span class="badge badge-success">Database</span></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li class="mt-2"><u>Tables with columns</u> to store the data of your web application.</li>
                        <li class="mt-2"><u>Stored procedures</u> to communicate the tables with the back-end 
                            through functions stored in the database.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><span class="badge badge-success">Back-end</span></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li class="mt-2"><u>C# models</u> which are C# classes. They contain the columns of each table
                            but in the form of C# properties. It also contains the functions that
                            communicate with the stored procedures of each table.</li>
                        <li class="mt-2"><u>C# services</u> which are C# classes. These classes are dedicated to the
                            user's business. Here, accesses to C# models are processed, emails are sent,
                            third-party APIs are connected and more.</li>
                        <li class="mt-2"><u>C# protocols/interfaces</u>. These interfaces are the connection between the
                            Web API's of the application with the C# services.</li>
                        <li class="mt-2"><u>C# Web API's</u>. These are the ones in charge of intercepting the HTTP requests
                            of the users and delegating the tasks to the C# services.</li>
                        <li class="mt-2"><u>C# filters</u>. Filters in a back-end allow you to block malicious or faulty
                            requests. If an HTTP request passes the filter, it executes the corresponding
                            web API.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><span class="badge badge-success">Front-end</span></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li class="mt-2"><u>TypeScript models</u>. These are models which contain the names of the columns
                            stored in each table, but in property format.</li>
                        <li class="mt-2"><u>jQuery code</u>. This layer is in charge of taking the interactions by the user
                            to send or retrieve information from the API's. It also connects with
                            TypeScript models.</li>
                        <li class="mt-2"><u>Razor Pages</u>. Razor pages are responsible for giving rise to HTML, CSS and
                            JavaScript code. Every Razor page has a back-end that is only accessed if
                            the C# filters are passed.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="card bg-secondary" id="4">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <img class="card-img-top" src="/img/FiyiStack/Languages.png" alt="Languages">
                    <h5 class="card-title">4. The languages that FiyiStack works with</h5>
                    <p>FiyiStack works with <span class="badge badge-success">6 languages</span> at the moment:</p>
                    <ol>
                        <li>HTML</li>
                        <li>CSS</li>
                        <li>JavaScript</li>
                        <li>TypeScript</li>
                        <li>C#</li>
                        <li>T-SQL</li>
                    </ol>
                     <div class="alert alert-info alert-dismissible fade show" role="alert">
                        <span class="alert-inner--icon"><i class="ni ni-bell-55"></i></span>
                        <span class="alert-inner--text">New languages will be added later</span>
                    </div>
              </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>